 ESP32 Modular File Server Features:
Modular Design:

StorageManager Class: Handles both Flash and SD card operations
WebServerManager Class: Manages all API endpoints and routing
Reusable functions: Easy to copy/paste for other projects

Key Features:

Dual Storage Support: Automatically detects SD card availability
RESTful API: Clean endpoints for storage info, file listing, and downloads
Memory Efficient: Streams files instead of loading into memory
Activity Tracking: Monitors requests and client connections

🌐 Web App Features:
Smart Download Management:

IndexedDB Integration: Files are cached locally after download
Download Status Tracking: Visual indicators for downloaded files
Offline Mode: Works without ESP32 connection using cached files
Storage Selection: User can choose between Flash and SD card

Modern UI:

Responsive Design: Works on desktop and mobile
Real-time Stats: System monitoring with auto-refresh
Progress Indicators: Loading states and download feedback
Glass-morphism Design: Modern, attractive interface

Advanced Features:

File Management: Clear downloads, view storage info
Error Handling: Graceful fallbacks and user feedback
Auto-reconnection: Detects when ESP32 comes back online
File Caching: Downloaded files persist between sessions

📋 Usage Instructions:

ESP32 Setup: Flash the code, connects creates "FileServer-ESP32" WiFi network
Web Access: Connect to WiFi and visit the IP address shown in serial monitor
File Download: Select storage location, browse files, click download
Offline Access: Downloaded files remain available even when ESP32 is disconnected

🔄 Reusable Pattern:
Both components are designed as modules you can easily copy and adapt:

ESP32: Copy the StorageManager and WebServerManager classes
Web: Copy the FileDownloaderManager class and associated HTML/CSS
Customization: Easy to modify for different file types, storage locations, or UI themes

The system automatically handles storage detection, file caching, offline mode, and provides a smooth user experience. Perfect for educational projects, IoT file distribution, or any scenario where you need to serve files from ESP32 storage!